<heading id="3E1D4846FFF8FFC7FF71FBB0FDBFFBD2" bold="true" box="[151,578,1122,1149]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="4">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FF71FBB0FDBFFBD2" authority="(Saalmuller, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Saalmuller" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[151,578,1122,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boseae">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FF71FBB0FDBFFBD2" bold="true" box="[151,578,1122,1149]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FF71FBB0FE9FFBD3" bold="true" box="[151,354,1122,1149]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Eudocima boseae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFF8FFC7FE97FBB0FDC7FBD2" author="Saalmuller, M." box="[369,570,1122,1148]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="258 - 310" refId="ref39857" refString="Saalmuller, M. (1880) Neue Lepidopteren aus Madagascar, die sich in Museum der Senckenberg'schen naturforschenden Gesellschaft befinden. Bericht uber die Senckenbergische Naturforschende Gesellschaft in Frankfurt a. M., 1879 - 1880, 258 - 310." type="journal article" year="1880">Saalmüller, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFF8FFC7FF71FB55FAEEFAD7" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF8FFC7FF71FB55FD8CFB0F" blockId="16.[151,1436,1122,1401]" box="[151,625,1159,1185]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFF8FFC7FF79FB55FF14FB0F" box="[159,233,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1923,1947]" captionTargetBox="[217,1371,196,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-32@62.[206,1381,181,1899]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 9. Eudocima materna group and African Eudocima adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605516/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 9</figureCitation>
: E–F, 19: C, 24: J–L, 31: A, 92: D)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF8FFC7FF71FB79FAEEFAD7" blockId="16.[151,1436,1122,1401]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This is a sexually dimorphic species with a banded black, red and yellow abdomen unique to the genus. It is one of only two 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FEC7FB1DFE6EFB47" box="[289,403,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FEC7FB1DFE6EFB47" box="[289,403,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Eudocima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where the dorsal hindwing medial patch is fused with the marginal band; the other species, 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FF71FB21FED6FAA2" box="[151,299,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FF71FB21FEDAFAA2" baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[151,295,1267,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperator">E. imperator</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
has an orange dorsal abdomen and a checkered hindwing fringe like other African 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FB3EFB21FAB7FAA3" box="[1240,1354,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FB3EFB21FAB7FAA3" box="[1240,1354,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Eudocima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FABEFB21FEDFFA9F" baseAuthorityName="Saalmuller" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boseae">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FABEFB21FEDFFA9F" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Eudocima boseae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only Old World 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FDC7FAC5FD17FA9F" box="[545,746,1303,1329]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FDC7FAC5FD6EFA9F" box="[545,659,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Eudocima</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with a double medial patch, although this condition occurs in several New World species including 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FDD8FAE9FC00FAFB" box="[574,1021,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FDD8FAE9FD2BFAFA" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[574,726,1339,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorans">E. memorans</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FD07FAE9FC89FAFB" authorityName="Phalaena" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[737,884,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collusoria">E. collusoria</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FC99FAE9FC04FAFB" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[895,1017,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colubra">E. colubra</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FBD2FAE9FB2AFAFB" box="[1076,1239,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FBD2FAE9FB2EFAFB" box="[1076,1235,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sepentifera">E. sepentifera</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The female has a narrow green transverse band which is not found in any New World taxa. It is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF8FFC7FB60FA8DFAF2FAD7" box="[1158,1295,1375,1401]" name="Madagascar" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
